How Worried Should We Be About Screen Time During the Pandemic?

The coronavirus pandemic ended the screen time debate: Screens won. We all now find ourselves on our screens for school, for work and for connecting with family and friends during this time of social distancing and increased isolation.

But should we be worried about this excessive screen use right now? Or should we finally get over it and embrace the benefits of our digital devices?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am not talking about the obvious physical changes like the fact that we are all getting fat and our eyesight is getting worse.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But there are also many negative consequences which we are just beginning to understand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Or do we mostly just use our devices to distract ourselves from the world around us?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am not saying that we should all go back to the old days of sitting in front of the TV for hours on end.
